/**
 * Cross-process handshake for the active Studio session in this worktree.
 * `createStudioSession` writes the session id (and serviceUrl + pid) here on launch;
 * `openTracePlan` (and any future Studio-aware command) reads it to decide
 * whether to route into the existing tab or spawn a new chromeless window.
 *
 * Keyed by the host coding agent's session id when one is exposed, so two
 * agents sharing a single worktree keep separate records; falls back to a hash
 * of `process.cwd()` otherwise. Single slot per scope: a second
 * `createStudioSession` in the same scope is treated as a replacement and wins.
 * The browser tab can outlive the CLI process, so reads do NOT check pid
 * liveness; the navigation layer handles that.
 *
 * Only STABLE per-session ids are used (the file is a cross-process handshake,
 * so the writer and a later reader must resolve the same scope). Per-request
 * ids (e.g. `CURSOR_TRACE_ID`) are deliberately excluded.
 *
 * Mirrors `activePreviewSession.ts` shape and atomicity guarantees.
 */
